@{_Section "Preface"}

@{b}Spitfireý@{ub} is offered to you under the concept of @{i}Shareware@{ui}. You may use @{b}Spitfireý@{ub} for an evaluation period of up to 30 days without paying any fee. If you are going to use @{i}Spitfireý@{ui} after the evaluation period, you have to register.@{par}

See @{"License" link "License"} and @{"Shareware" link "Registration"} for more information.@{par}
@endnode

@node "About" "About"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Preface"


@{_Section "About Spitfireý"}

Spitfireý is a Palm Desktop for the AmigaOS. It provides a connection to 3Com's Palm computer or compatibles, and allows a user to HotSync these devices with their Amiga.@{par}

The entire Spitfireý package provides the following main capabilities:@{par}


@{_bullet}Allows working with PalmOS applications on your Amiga.  Spitfireý provides Date Book, Address Book, To Do List, and Memo Pad applications of the PalmOS so you can view, enter and modify any data stored on your handheld device.@{LIndent 2}


@{_bullet}HotSync synchroniztion which enables you to backup the data stored on your handheld device, and synchronize the data with Spitfireý.@{LIndent 2}


@{_bullet}Import and export capabilities so you can use existing database files as the basis of Address Book or Memo Pad entries.@{LIndent 2}




@{_Section "Summary of features"}

Spitfireý supports the following main features:@{par}

@{_bullet}Partial, Mirror and Full backup of Palm databases and files.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Restoring of Palm databases and files.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Multiple user support.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Installation of PalmOS files and databases.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}AmigaOS equivalents of PalmOS Memo Pad, To Do List, Address Book, and Date Book.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Full Synchronizing of Memo Pad, To Do List, Address Book, and Date Book with AmigaOS desktop.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Import/Export of Memos in ASCII format.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Import/Export of Addresses in CSV format.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Import/Export of Address with Contact Manager.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Easy configurability with support for any serial device.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Modular design for easy expansion.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}One button HotSyncing!@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Localization.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Easy to use interface, with all the customization features of MUI@{LIndent 2}

@{LIndent 0}

@endnode



@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@next "License"
@prev "Features"


@{_Section "Requirements"}

@{_bullet}Amiga with 020/2Mb or better.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}An available serial port.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}Palm Pilot or compatible with it's cradle plugged into a serial port.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}AmigaOS 3.0 or greater.@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}MUI 3.8 or greater.@{LIndent 2}

    - third-party MCC classes:@{par}
      ñ TextInput@{par}
      ñ NList@{par}
      ñ MonthNavigator@{par}
      ñ DateText@{par}
      ñ DateString@{par}
      ñ TimeText@{par}
      ñ TimeString@{par}
@{_bullet}pdalink.library@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}date.library@{LIndent 2}

@{_bullet}vapor_toolkit.library@{LIndent 2}


The install script will properly install all necessary parts from the Spitfireý archive.@{par}

@endnode



